<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-685-326  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 685 326.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  May 31 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Elcon announces MS-Windows terminal emulator. (Elcon TechnologyCorp.) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Blankenhorn, Dana.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Elcon Technology Corp. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Microsoft Windows 3.0 (Graphical user interface) (usage)Access for Windows (Computer terminal emulator) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionEmulators.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>EICON ANNOUNCES MS-WINDOWS TERMINAL EMULATOR MONTREAL, QUEBEC, CANADA, 1990MAY 22 (NB) -- Eicon Technology announced Access for Windows, a 3270 terminalemulation package that runs under Microsoft Windows 3.0.andM;It provides full IBM mainframe terminal functionality under Windows whileallowing other Windows applications to run at the same time.andP;  Access forWindows supports Multiple Document Interface and Dynamic Data Exchange, twokey Windows features, and emulates the 3278 Display Models 2-5, 3279 colordisplay, and 3287 printers, as well as 3270 S3G graphics, 3270-PC filetransfer, and full support of APL/APL2.andP;  It also provides an applicationprogramming interface which is fully compatible with IBM EHLLAPIspecifications, as well as editing features of Windows and macro recordings.andM;Finally, the program allows users to easily customize their keyboards,remapping keys through a graphical representation of the keyboard on thescreen.andP;  This makes the program easy to customize in other languages,allowing full character translation tables for up to 17 different countries.andO;The software ships in July.andM;(Dana Blankenhorn/19900529/Press Contact: Cynthia Yacowar, Eicon Technology,514-631-2592)</TEXT></DOC>